article.headline: St. Francis, NY 71, Fairleigh Dickinson 69
article.story: HACKENSACK, N.J. (AP) -- Robert Hines had 25 points and hit two key free throws in the closing seconds to lead St. Francis of New York to a 71-69 win over Fairleigh Dickinson on Friday night. Allan Sheppard added 12 points and Bassith Yessoufou finished with 10 points and seven rebounds for the Terriers (6-19, 4-9 in Northeast Conference). Manny Ubilla scored 25 points -- including six 3-pointers -- to lead the Knights (12-11, 7-5), while Cameron Tyler and Andre Harris each scored 14 points and pulled down eight rebounds. FDU never trailed until Hines' jumper with about six minutes left gave St. Francis 61-59 lead. The two teams then traded baskets for the rest of the game, but the Terriers went ahead for good when Jamaal Womack sank two free throws in the closing minute. The Knights then turned the ball over and Hines hit his foul shots with eight seconds left to give St. Francis a 70-66 lead. Ubilla then hit a 3-pointer with two seconds left, but Sheppard then sealed the win with free throw.
